For the case of `Redirect`, it is possible to set the `Location` header plus an appropriate status code manually. This is much easier now that we have `#[derive(Responder)]`:

(disclaimer: completely untested)
```rust
use rocket::http::hyper::header::Location;

#[derive(Responder)]
#[response(status=303)]
struct RawRedirect((), Location);

fn get_redirected() -> RawRedirect {
    RawRedirect((), Location(format!("{}#{}", uri!(destination_route: params...), "fragment/data")))
}
```

This approach is not without its downsides (e.g. needing to manually percent-encode the fragment) and it would definitely be more ergonomic for users if Rocket had first-class support for this.

